Section 1:
1 L.D. 1098
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 EDUCATION AND CULTURAL AFFAIRS
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 720, L.D. 1098, “An Act to Ensure
10 Equal Access to a Full School Day for All Students”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'Resolve, Directing the Department of Education to Review the Use of Abbreviated
13 School Days'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
15 'Sec. 1. Abbreviated school day; review. Resolved: That the Department of
16 Education shall, within existing resources, review the use of the abbreviated school day
17 provisions described in department rule 05-071 C.M.R. Chapter 101: Maine Unified
18 Special Education Regulation Birth to Age Twenty-Two in schools in the State. The
19 Department of Education may consult with the Maine Education Policy Research Institute
20 to complete the review and requirements of the report described in section 2.
21 Sec. 2. Report. Resolved: That the Department of Education shall submit a report
22 no later than February 1, 2026 to the Joint Standing Committee on Education and Cultural
23 Affairs on the findings of the review described in section 1. The report must include data
24 regarding the frequency and duration of abbreviated school day placements and input from
25 stakeholders, including, but not limited to, school personnel and parents. The report must
26 also include information about the impacts that abbreviated school day placements may
27 have on school funding and on student outcomes. The Joint Standing Committee on
28 Education and Cultural Affairs may report out a bill based on the report to the Second
29 Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature.'
30 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
31 number to read consecutively.
32 SUMMARY
3333 This amendment replaces the bill with a resolve. The amendment directs the
3344 Department of Education to review the use of abbreviated school day rule provisions in
Page 1 - 132LR1267(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 720, L.D. 1098
315 schools in the State and requires the department to submit a report on the findings of that
326 review to the Joint Standing Committee on Education and Cultural Affairs. The report
337 must include data on the use of abbreviated school day placements, stakeholder input and
348 information on the impacts abbreviated school day placements may have on school funding
359 and student outcomes. The Joint Standing Committee on Education and Cultural Affairs
460 may report out a bill based on the report to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd
471 Legislature.
482 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
493 (See attached)
Page 2 - 132LR1267(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
